    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Three dysfunctional roles — Victim, Persecutor, Rescuer — that agents must recognise and redirect."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Karpman Drama Triangle"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#SocialPenetrationTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Altman & Taylor: self-disclosure depth and breadth as trust-building signals."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Social Penetration Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#MotivationalInterviewing_Theory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Rollnick & Miller: resolving ambivalence by eliciting change talk and rolling with resistance."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Motivational Interviewing Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#AttachmentTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Bowlby/Ainsworth: secure, anxious, avoidant, and disorganised attachment styles affecting rapport strategies."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Attachment Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#RelevanceTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Sperber & Wilson: listeners minimise processing effort while maximising cognitive effects. Implemented as real-time weight modifier on graph traversal paths."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Relevance Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#BDI_Model",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Agent reasoning framework: Belief (current knowledge), Desire (target state), Intention (committed next action)."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Belief-Desire-Intention Model"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#TransactionalAnalysis",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Eric Berne's ego-state model (Parent/Adult/Child) governing agent routing via ego-state detection."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Transactional Analysis"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#WinnersTriangle",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Choy's replacement framework: Vulnerable (from Victim), Assertive (from Persecutor), Caring (from Rescuer)."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Winner's Triangle"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#CognitiveLoadTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Sweller: intrinsic, extraneous, germane load — governs Relevance Theory routing in UCKB."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Cognitive Load Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#CommunicationAccommodationTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Giles CAT: convergence (rapport-building) and divergence (authority/identity assertion) dynamics."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Communication Accommodation Theory"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://uckb.io/ontology#PolyVagalTheory",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual",
      "https://uckb.io/ontology#PsychologicalModel"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Porges: autonomic nervous system states (ventral vagal, sympathetic, dorsal vagal) mapped to de-escalation protocols."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@value": "Polyvagal Theory"
      }
    ]
  }
]